REYNOLDS, Appellant, v. PATTEN, Respondent. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. February 5, 1894.) Appeal from city court. Action by Martin Reynolds against Thomas Patten, impleaded, etc.

Argued before DALY, C. J., and BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

Johnston & Johnston, for appellant. Deyo, Dun & Baurdorf, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion for reargument granted. See 25 N. Y. Supp. 100.
